<span id="iv.XI-p2"></span> ————————————

<span id="iv.XI-p3"></span>*Argument—Here begins the second part* <span
id="fr_444"></span>[445](#fn_444.md) *of this work, which treats of the
origin, history, and destinies of the two cities, the earthly and the
heavenly.  In the first place, Augustin shows in this book how the two
cities were formed originally, by the separation of the good and bad
angels; and takes occasion to treat of the creation of the world, as it
is described in Holy Scripture in the beginning of the book of Genesis.*

